However, this tool does not have as many filter options that we can use. So it is always worth considering whether we can use the locate command or instead use the find command. It always depends on what we are looking for.

find / searches the entire filesystem, which includes many directories you may not have permission to read.
find / → search whole filesystem
-type f → only files
-name "*.conf" → config files
-size +25k → larger than 25KB
-size -25k → smaller than 25KB
-newermt 2020-03-03 → modified after March 3, 2020
2>/dev/null → hides permission denied errors






















